              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 Bad Request', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "pm.test('Error mentions weightage', () => {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const text = JSON.stringify(body).toLowerCase();",
                  "    pm.expect(text).to.include.oneOf(['weight', '100']);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Token {{token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Incomplete KR\",\n  \"metric_label\": \"Units\",\n  \"type\": \"numeric\",\n  \"start_value\": 0,\n  \"target_value\": 100,\n  \"current_value\": 0,\n  \"unit\": \"units\",\n  \"owner_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"due_date\": \"2026-09-30\",\n  \"weightage\": 50\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/zenko/api/v1/organizations/{{org_id}}/objectives/{{obj_id}}/key-results/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["zenko", "api", "v1", "organizations", "{{org_id}}", "objectives", "{{obj_id}}", "key-results", ""]
            },
            "description": "**Negative test.** Sends a single KR with `weightage: 50`. Since 50% ≠ 100%, the API must reject this with **HTTP 400**.\n\nThe automated test asserts the 400 status and that the error message references weightage or 100.\n\n**Prerequisite:** The objective must have no existing KRs (so the running total after this KR would be 50%, not 100%). If you ran the bulk replace earlier, delete those KRs first or use a fresh objective."
